    <note>Yuan(2) Jiang [2112] His ancestors belonged to a great Wei(2) Shi lineage (daxing) of Fuzhou, Linchuan xian. He is listed, along with Shouwen [19827] and Fengzong [19832], as Jianchang, Nancheng county jinshi in the Jiangxi TZ. Since Nancheng was a county under the jurisdiction of Fuzhou before Song and was probably established from the ancient territory of Linchuan, this must have been the ancestral home. His grandfather, Dezhao [4139], served the kingdom of Wuyue as chief minister of state and was granted the surname Yuan(2). Jiang was a Qiantang person who lived in Suzhou and had degrees listed in both local histories. His cousin, Xiangzong [4138], a Yuhang resident, was the son-in-law of Qian(1) Shu [3037], the last king of Wuyue, who voluntarily returned the territory under his control to Song. Shu's second son was Qian(1) Weiyan [8006]. Jiang was Haowen's [7410] nephew, Li(2) Pingyi's [1068] father-in-law, father of Ouyang(1) Xiu's [1384] grandson-in-law, Yuan(2) Qibi [4137], and grandfather-in-law of Su(1) Song's [8116] son, Xi(b) [3758]. Fan Zhongyan, WJ, 12.3b; Jiangxi TZ, 21.12b; XCB, 173.17b, 174.13a, 196.3a-3b, 243.1a, 255.6b, 256.13b, 271.9b; Xianchun Linan zhi, 65.3b; SHY:ZG, 65.38a-38b; SS, 343.1a; Suzhou FZ, 139.20a, 145.9a; Su Song, WJ, 52.1a-12a; Wang Anli, WJ, 7.18a-26b; Wujun zhi, 28.2b. CBD, 1, 88-89.</note>
